content.description: Start on 2 crimps.  Move left into an undercling and trick your way up the face.
content.location: On the back of the Glory or Die Boulder.  Or 150 above the trail intersection on the west side of the north shore beach.  A safer climb than it looks.

climbs.name: Trump Bucks
climbs.fa: Ian CB and Anna Boatman probably

content.description: Kinda fun.. Sit start the short overhanging arete with a sidepull for the left hand and right on the arete on a pretty good spot.  Grade may differ depending on method..:)
content.location: 40 feet south of the snake charmer boulder.. aka 100 feet above a bench in the grass of the north shore beach.

content.description: Start sitting kind of awkwardly on low good holds, do a hard pull to the nice flat big hold, and do some tricky and powerful moves up the blunt arete to good holds at the top.  Great moves
content.location: About 200 feet up the hill on the west side of the North shore beach and a little bit north.

climbs.name: Monumental
climbs.fa: Ian CB, Mike Lohre, Vince Evans, or Old School

content.description: Short burly compression arete on Glory or Die Boulder.  Start crouching, and slap up the refridgerator like arete.  Short but good moves, cool topout.
content.protection: 1-2 pads as long as you climb carefully.
content.location: About 200 feet up the hill on the west side of the North shore beach.

content.description: Establish on under-cling and work your way up the thin face.
content.location: About 20 feet below Snake Charmer in the talus. This is the first problem in the talus facing the lake.

climbs.name: Glory or Death
climbs.fa: Ian CB, Mike Lohre, or Old School

content.description: Climb up the center of the downhill facing side of the Glory or Death Boulder from a stand on nice side pulls.  Great moves above a very poor landing.  If you have enough pads it's doable..
content.protection: As many pads as you have or don't fall.  Scary death pit landing.
content.location: About 200 feet up the hill on the west side of the North shore beach.

content.description: Climb the left side of the arete on the Glory or Death Boulder.  Really fun.
content.protection: As many pads as you got or just don't fall.  Not incredibly tall, but a death pit landing.
content.location: About 200 feet up the hill on the west side of the North shore beach.

content.description: Start on the low blocky feature as per Snake Charmer.  Do the move to the ledge, then head to the right through the crack and steep roof.
content.location: Park in the first lot on the North entrance road.  Walk down the trail toward the beach to a bench at the bottom of the hill.  Follow the faint trail behind the bench into the talus, then head up and slightly right to the Snake Charmer boulder.  Faces downhill.

content.description: Just next to Snake Charmer, pull on the overhang from a stand above the hole, right hand on a cool incut crimper flake, left hand on a sidepull. Do a tough and committing feeling move to the lip and top out left or right.
content.location: 150 feet above the trail intersection on the west side of the North shore beach.

content.description: A low boulder with a serpentine bulge.
